original_sentence: - SP CSI-RS resource set ID: This field contains an index of NZP-CSI-RS-ResourceSet containing Semi Persistent NZP CSI-RS resources, as specified in TS 38.331 [5], indicating the Semi Persistent NZP CSI-RS resource set, which shall be activated or deactivated. The length of the field is 6 bits; - IM: This field indicates the presence of the octet containing SP CSI-IM resource set ID field. If the IM field is set to 1 , the octet containing SP CSI-IM resource set ID field is present. If IM field is set to 0 , the octet containing SP CSI-IM resource set ID field is not present;
